-- Schaeuble: paying 3 tranches to Greece together is under discussion
-- 
-- Tue Nov 13, 2012 11:28am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/11/13/us-eurozone-greece-tranches-idUSBRE8AC0SH20121113

 

 BRUSSELS  (Reuters) - EU finance ministers met on Tuesday seeking to break an impasse over a new regime to supervise banks, but with much of the plan contested and time running short to agree. 
 Their talks followed a meeting of euro zone finance ministers where disagreement between Greece's international lenders over how long to give Athens to get its debts down to a sustainable level reignited fears that the euro zone debt crisis could flare anew. For highlights of comments from ministers and officials after the talks click on: [ID:nL5E8MD30I] (Brussels newsroom)